definition[0]: to continue with a plan or an activity, especially in a determined way
example[0]: Quinlan decided to push ahead with the deal.
definition[1]: to continue with a plan or activity, especially in a determined way
example[1]: The government is determined to push ahead with its economic reforms.
definition[2]: if prices on a financial market push ahead, they rise
example[2]: The Composite Index pushed ahead 3.77 to 466.56.
